  <description><![CDATA[<p>The stylish Hotel Gotthard is in the centre of Lech and has been family run for three generations. It started out as a small bakery in the 1930s, and has remained in the family ever since. With an on-site micro-brewery serving up cold beers and a café baking fresh bread and cakes, it's easy to see why we love this hotel. </p>
<h2>Home-brewed beer</h2>
<p><span>If you're looking for the perfect après ski drink, the Hotel Gotthard boasts its own micro-brewery. Enjoy a pint of beer in the hotel's cosy bar or out on the sun terrace. If beer isn't for you, the hotel owners also distil their own schnapps and mountain herb gin which feature perfectly in a signature cocktail.</span></p>
<p><span>The hotel's wine offering is top-notch with a huge selection from their cellar.</span></p>
<p><span>Chill out in the evening in the Sports Lounge with snooker, </span>billiards and ping pong table.</p>
<h2>Pool with a view</h2>
<p>What could be better than relaxing in a heated pool surrounded by the mountains. The hotel's small outdoor pool offers excellent views of the snowy peaks.</p>
<p>The wellness area also features a large indoor pool with whirlpool and massage jets, a relaxation area, and a sauna area (nude, open to ages 15+ only) with Finnish and bio saunas, steam room and waterbeds. There is also a textile and family sauna that everyone can use (with swimwear).</p>
<h2>Authentic food</h2>
<p>With its roots as a bakery, food is at the heart of the Hotel Gotthard and they still bake their own bread and pastries in the bakery today, just in time for you to enjoy at breakfast each morning.</p>
<p>The hotel's talented chefs treat you to a four course dinner in the evening.</p>
<p>The on-site Café Gotthard is a must-visit too for some warm apple strudel and freshly brewed coffee.</p>]]></description>
